What Does Jones Fracture Mean For Durant? ESPN injury analyst Stephania Bell explains what a "Jones fracture" is and how the injury will affect Kevin Durant. Tags: Kevin Durant, Oklahoma City Thunder, NBA What Does Jones Fracture Mean For Durant? At the start of the 1985-86 NBA season, you might recall Michael Jordan suffering a foot fracture that sidelined him for nearly 4½ months. Understand Jordan's injury was to the navicular bone, which is a more rare and worrisome injury (it ended Yao Ming's career in Houston and is what likely will sideline Sixers 2014 first-round pick Joel Embiid for an entire season) than the "Jones fracture" sustained by Kevin Durant. Most of the reporting maintains Durant should be cleared to play in about six to eight weeks, though Oklahoma City Thunder general manager Sam Presti has offered no exact timetable. However, a sustained absence like Jordan's appears unlikely. To read more of Dr. Mark Adickes' prognosis of Kevin Durant's broken foot, become an Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits » Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Dr. Mark Adickes Follow Archive All-American, Baylor University Player, USFL, 1984-86 Player, NFL, 1986-91 MD, Harvard Medical School Assistant professor, Department of Orthopedic Surgery, University of Texas Medical School Co-medical director, Ironman Sports Medicine Institute, Memorial Hermann Former team physician, U.S. Ski Team Former team physician, Houston Rockets, NBA